text.tspan: IPv6 clients are supported for TCP traffic if you configure the load balancer in Premium Tier. IPv6 clients aren’t supported for UDP traffic.
Another reason to choose External Network Load Balancing is if you need to ensure that the load balancer is located in a particular region.
External network load balancers use regional external IP addresses that are accessible by clients anywhere.
Clients in a VPC network or in a network connected to a VPC network.
